docs.lead_paragraph: LIMA, Peru — Peru’s presidential election is headed for a runoff, with Pedro Castillo, a far-left former union activist and teacher, in the lead, according to data released Monday by the country’s electoral body.

docs.lead_paragraph: QUITO, Ecuador — Guillermo Lasso, a 66-year-old conservative former banker, was set to win Ecuador’s presidential election and beat out Andrés Arauz, a 36-year-old leftist handpicked by former President Rafael Correa.

headline.main: Conservative Ex-Banker Headed to Victory in Presidential Election in Ecuador
headline.print_headline: Ecuador’s Presidential Election to Bolster Influence of Indigenous Party

docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — The Hong Kong government on Tuesday introduced the final details of a push to drastically overhaul the city’s election system, including a proposal that would make it illegal to encourage voters to cast blank ballots or boycott elections.
